   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_unknown_02_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#1-North-Audley-Street_ENK">1 North Audley Street</placeName>
                  <lb/>Monday Eve<hi rend="superscript">[unclear]n[/unclear]</hi>
                  <lb/>
                  <lb/>
               </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Dear Sir I am much obliged<lb/>to you for Puss - a most elegant<lb/>Dandy he is -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>Since I saw you<persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Wilson</persName>has<lb/>seen<persName ref="./Personography.xml#DaviJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Davis</persName>the gentleman<lb/>who has written the best books<lb/>we have on<placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#CN">China</placeName>-<persName ref="./Personography.xml#DaviJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.<choice>
                     <orig>D</orig>
                     <reg>Davis</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName>says<lb/>that his history of<placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#CN">China</placeName>has been<lb/>translated into French; but<lb/>he has written<title ref="./Workography.xml#Sketch2">"<hi rend="underline">sketches of China</hi>"</title>
               <lb/>which as far as he knows<lb/>have not been translated -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I wish you would be so good<lb/>to send to<persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParkE1">Madame Belloc</persName>a<lb/>copy of<persName ref="./Personography.xml#DaviJ1">Davis</persName>'s<title ref="./Workography.xml#Sketch2">Sketches of China</title>
               <lb/>(published by<persName ref="./Personography.xml#KnigC1">Knight</persName>) You have<lb/>means probably of conveying<lb/>the book to her more<choice>
                  <orig>expedi-<lb/>tiously</orig>
                  <reg>expeditiously</reg>
               </choice>to her than I could -<lb/>and you know that expedition<lb/>is more than half the battle<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_unknown_02_page02.jpg"/>in these cases -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>I am not quite ready<lb/>yet to talk to you about my<lb/>own affairs - When I am I<lb/>will write to you again</p>
            <lb/>
            <closer>Meanwhile I am<lb/>Yours truly - obliged<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ParkE1">Madame<choice>
                        <orig>Bellocs</orig>
                        <reg>Belloc's</reg>
                     </choice>
                  </persName>[unclear]address[/unclear] of<lb/>course you know but<lb/>I can do no harm by<lb/>adding it here -<lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Rue-de-Medicine-5_FR">Rue de l'Ecole de Medicine<lb/>N<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>5</placeName>
               </p>
               <lb/>
